; Regression test for the lower-bound off-by-one in exception table dispatch.
;
; With useExceptionTables, the range check is `pc >= entry.0`. But `pc` is
; incremented *before* each instruction executes, so when the instruction at
; `startPc - 4` throws, `pc == startPc == entry.0` and the check incorrectly
; fires the catch handler.
;
; The instruction at startPc - 4 in `(1 (try ...))` is ASSERT_FUNC (which peeks
; without popping, so the stack depth matches entry.2). On tier 0 (TRY/CATCH
; opcodes) ASSERT_FUNC fires before TRY executes, so the handlers stack is
; empty and the exception propagates to the outer catch. On tier 1 (exception
; tables) ASSERT_FUNC incorrectly triggers the inner catch.
;
; `flag` starts false. The inner catch body sets it true. The outer catch
; returns flag. Correct result: false. Buggy result: true.
(set flag false)
--
=> false
==
(try
  (1 (try { (set flag true) "ok" } e "inner"))
  outer
  flag)
--
=> false
--
